#: ../../../repositories.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Learn how to set up and manage package repositories in Spack, enabling you "
"to maintain custom packages and override built-in ones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:13
msgid "Package Repositories (repos.yaml)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:15
msgid ""
"Spack comes with thousands of built-in package recipes. As of Spack v1.0, "
"these are hosted in a separate Git repository at `spack/spack-packages "
"<https://github.com/spack/spack-packages>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:18
msgid ""
"A **package repository** is a directory that Spack searches when it needs to "
"find a package by name. You may need to maintain packages for restricted, "
"proprietary, or experimental software separately from the built-in "
"repository. Spack allows you to configure local and remote repositories "
"using either the ``repos.yaml`` configuration file or the ``spack repo`` "
"command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:22
msgid ""
"This document describes how to set up and manage these package repositories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:25
msgid "Structure of an Individual Package Repository"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:27
msgid ""
"An individual Spack package repository is a directory structured as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:29
msgid ""
"/path/to/repos/                   # the top-level dir is added to the Python "
"search path\n"
"  spack_repo/                     # every package repository is part of the "
"spack_repo Python module\n"
"    myrepo/                       # directory for the 'myrepo' repository "
"(matches namespace)\n"
"      repo.yaml                   # configuration file for this package "
"repository\n"
"      packages/                   # directory containing package "
"directories\n"
"        hdf5/                     # directory for the hdf5 package\n"
"          package.py              # the package recipe file\n"
"        mpich/                    # directory for the mpich package\n"
"          package.py              # the package recipe file\n"
"          mpich-1.9-bugfix.patch  # example patch file\n"
"        trilinos/\n"
"          package.py\n"
"    ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:45
msgid ""
"``repo.yaml``. This file contains metadata for this specific repository, for "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:48
msgid ""
"repo:\n"
"  namespace: myrepo\n"
"  api: v2.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:54
msgid "It defines primarily:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:56
msgid ""
"``namespace``. A unique identifier for this repository (e.g., ``myrepo``, "
"``projectx``). See the :ref:`Namespaces <namespaces>` section for more "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:59
msgid ""
"``api``. The version of the Spack Package API this repository adheres to (e."
"g., ``v2.0``). Spack itself defines what range of API versions it supports, "
"and will error if it encounters a repository with an unsupported API version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:63
msgid ""
"``packages/``. This directory contains subdirectories for each package in "
"the repository. Each package directory contains a ``package.py`` file and "
"any patches or other files needed to build the package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:67
msgid "Package repositories allow you to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:69
msgid "Maintain your own packages separately from Spack's built-in set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:70
msgid ""
"Share your packages (e.g., by hosting them on a shared file system or in a "
"Git repository) without committing them to the main ``spack/spack-packages`` "
"repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:71
msgid "Override built-in Spack packages with your own implementations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:73
msgid ""
"Packages in a separate repository can also *depend on* built-in Spack "
"packages, allowing you to leverage existing recipes without re-implementing "
"them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:76
msgid "Package Names"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:78
msgid ""
"Package names are defined by the directory names under ``packages/``. In the "
"example above, the package names are ``hdf5``, ``mpich``, and ``trilinos``. "
"Package names can only contain lowercase characters ``a-z``, digits ``0-9`` "
"and hyphens ``-``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:84
msgid ""
"Package names are **derived** from the directory names under ``packages/``. "
"Package directories are required to be valid Python module names, which "
"means they cannot contain hyphens or start with a digit. This means that a "
"package named ``my-package`` would be stored in a directory named "
"``my_package/``, and a package named ``7zip`` would be stored in a directory "
"named ``_7zip/`` with an underscore prefix to make it a valid Python module "
"name. The mapping between package names and directory names is one-to-one. "
"Use ``spack list`` to see how Spack resolves the package names from the "
"directory names."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:91
msgid "Configuring Repositories with ``repos.yaml``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:93
msgid ""
"Spack uses ``repos.yaml`` files found in its :ref:`configuration scopes "
"<configuration>` (e.g., ``~/.spack/``, ``etc/spack/``) to discover and "
"prioritize package repositories. Note that this ``repos.yaml`` (plural) "
"configuration file is distinct from the ``repo.yaml`` (singular) file within "
"each individual package repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:96
msgid "Spack supports two main types of repository configurations:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:99
msgid "Local Repositories (Path-based)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:101
msgid "You can point Spack to a repository on your local filesystem:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:103 ../../../repositories.rst:141
#: ../../../repositories.rst:153 ../../../repositories.rst:166
#: ../../../repositories.rst:223 ../../../repositories.rst:237
msgid "``~/.spack/repos.yaml``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:103
msgid ""
"repos:\n"
"  my_local_packages: /path/to/my_repository_root"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:110
msgid ""
"Here, ``/path/to/my_repository_root`` should be the directory containing "
"that repository's ``repo.yaml`` and ``packages/`` subdirectory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:113
msgid "Git-based Repositories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:115
msgid "Spack can clone and use repositories directly from Git URLs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:117
msgid ""
"repos:\n"
"  my_remote_repo: https://github.com/myorg/spack-custom-pkgs.git"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:123
msgid "Automatic Cloning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:125
msgid ""
"When Spack first encounters a Git-based repository configuration, it "
"automatically clones it. By default, these repositories are cloned into a "
"subdirectory within ``~/.spack/package_repos/``, named with a hash of the "
"repository URL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:128
msgid ""
"To change directories to the package repository, you can use ``spack cd --"
"repo [name]``. To find where a repository is cloned, you can use ``spack "
"location --repo [name]`` or ``spack repo list``. The ``name`` argument is "
"optional; if omitted, Spack will use the first package repository in "
"configuration order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:133
msgid "Customizing Clone Location"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:135
msgid ""
"The default clone location (``~/.spack/package_repos/<hashed_name>``) might "
"not be convenient for package maintainers who want to make changes to "
"packages. You can specify a custom local directory for Spack to clone a Git "
"repository into, or to use if the repository is already cloned there. This "
"is done using the ``destination`` key in ``repos.yaml`` or via the ``spack "
"repo set --destination`` command (see :ref:`cmd-spack-repo-set-destination`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:139
msgid "For example, to use ``~/custom_packages_clone`` for ``my_remote_repo``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:141
msgid ""
"repos:\n"
"  my_remote_repo:\n"
"    git: https://github.com/myorg/spack-custom-pkgs.git\n"
"    destination: ~/custom_packages_clone"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:150
msgid ""
"If the ``git`` URL is defined in a lower-precedence configuration (like "
"Spack's defaults for ``builtin``), you only need to specify the "
"``destination`` in your user-level ``repos.yaml``. Spack can make the "
"configuration changes for you using ``spack repo set --destination ~/spack-"
"packages builtin``, or you can directly edit your ``repos.yaml`` file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:153
msgid ""
"repos:\n"
"  builtin:\n"
"    destination: ~/spack-packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:162
msgid "Updating and pinning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:164
msgid "Repos can be pinned to a git branch, tag, or commit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:166
msgid ""
"repos:\n"
"  builtin:\n"
"    branch: releases/v2025.07\n"
"    # tag: v2025.07.0\n"
"    # commit: 6427933daecef74b981d1f773731aeace3b06ede"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:176
msgid ""
"The ``spack repo update`` command will update the repo on disk to match the "
"current state of the config. If the repo is pinned to a commit or tag, it "
"will ensure the repo on disk reflects that commit or tag. If the repo is "
"pinned to a branch or unpinned, ``spack repo update`` will pull the most "
"recent state of the branch (the default branch if unpinned)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:181
msgid "Git repositories need a package repo index"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:183
msgid ""
"A single Git repository can contain one or more Spack package repositories. "
"To enable Spack to discover these, the root of the Git repository should "
"contain a ``spack-repo-index.yaml`` file. This file lists the relative paths "
"to package repository roots within the git repo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:187
msgid ""
"For example, assume a Git repository at ``https://example.com/my_org/my_pkgs."
"git`` has the following structure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:189
msgid ""
"my_pkgs.git/\n"
"  spack-repo-index.yaml     # metadata file at the root of the Git repo\n"
"  ...\n"
"  spack_pkgs/\n"
"    spack_repo/\n"
"      my_org/\n"
"        comp_sci_packages/  # package repository for computer science "
"packages\n"
"          repo.yaml\n"
"          packages/\n"
"            hdf5/\n"
"              package.py\n"
"            mpich/\n"
"              package.py\n"
"        physics_packages/   # package repository for physics packages\n"
"          repo.yaml\n"
"          packages/\n"
"            gromacs/\n"
"              package.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:210
msgid ""
"The ``spack-repo-index.yaml`` in the root of ``https://example.com/my_org/"
"my_pkgs.git`` should look like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:212
msgid "``my_pkgs.git/spack-repo-index.yaml``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:212
msgid ""
"repo_index:\n"
"  paths:\n"
"  - spack_pkgs/spack_repo/my_org/comp_sci_packages\n"
"  - spack_pkgs/spack_repo/my_org/physics_packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:221
msgid "If ``my_pkgs.git`` is configured in ``repos.yaml`` as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:223
msgid ""
"repos:\n"
"  example_mono_repo: https://example.com/my_org/my_pkgs.git"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:230
msgid ""
"Spack will clone ``my_pkgs.git`` and look for ``spack-repo-index.yaml``. It "
"will then register two separate repositories based on the paths found (e.g., "
"``<clone_dir>/spack_pkgs/spack_repo/my_org/comp_sci_packages`` and "
"``<clone_dir>/spack_pkgs/spack_repo/my_org/physics_packages``), each with "
"its own namespace defined in its respective ``repo.yaml`` file. Thus, one "
"``repos.yaml`` entry for a Git mono-repo can lead to *multiple repositories* "
"being available to Spack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:234
msgid ""
"If you want only one of the package repositories from a Git mono-repo, you "
"can override the paths in your user-level ``repos.yaml``. For example, if "
"you only want the computer science packages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:237
msgid ""
"repos:\n"
"  example_mono_repo:\n"
"    git: https://example.com/my_org/my_pkgs.git\n"
"    paths:\n"
"    - spack_pkgs/spack_repo/my_org/comp_sci_packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:247
msgid ""
"The ``spack repo add`` command can help you set up these configurations "
"easily."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:250
msgid "The ``builtin`` Repository"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:252
msgid ""
"Spack's extensive collection of built-in packages resides at `spack/spack-"
"packages <https://github.com/spack/spack-packages>`_. By default, Spack is "
"configured to use this as a Git-based repository. The default configuration "
"in ``$spack/etc/spack/defaults/repos.yaml`` looks something like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:256
msgid ""
"repos:\n"
"  builtin:\n"
"    git: https://github.com/spack/spack-packages.git"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:265
msgid "Namespaces"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:267
msgid ""
"Every repository in Spack has an associated **namespace** defined in the "
"``namespace:`` key of its top-level ``repo.yaml`` file. For example, the "
"built-in repository (from ``spack/spack-packages``) has its namespace "
"defined as ``builtin``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:270
msgid "``repo.yaml`` of ``spack/spack-packages``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:270
msgid ""
"repo:\n"
"  namespace: builtin\n"
"  api: v2.0 # Or newer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:278
msgid ""
"Spack records the repository namespace of each installed package. For "
"example, if you install the ``mpich`` package from the ``builtin`` repo, "
"Spack records its fully qualified name as ``builtin.mpich``. This "
"accomplishes two things:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:282
msgid ""
"You can have packages with the same name from different namespaces installed "
"simultaneously."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:283
msgid ""
"You can easily determine which repository a package came from after it is "
"installed (more :ref:`below <namespace-example>`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:287
msgid ""
"The ``namespace`` defined in the package repository's ``repo.yaml`` is the "
"**authoritative source** for the namespace. It is *not* derived from the "
"local configuration in ``repos.yaml``. This means that the namespace is "
"determined by the repository maintainer, not by the user or local "
"configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:292
msgid "Nested Namespaces for Organizations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:294
msgid ""
"As we have already seen in the Git-based package repositories example above, "
"you can create nested namespaces by using periods in the namespace name. For "
"example, a repository for packages related to computation at LLNL might have "
"the namespace ``llnl.comp``, while one for physical and life sciences could "
"be ``llnl.pls``. On the file system, this requires a directory structure "
"like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:298
msgid ""
"/path/to/repos/\n"
"  spack_repo/\n"
"    llnl/\n"
"      comp/\n"
"        repo.yaml  # Contains namespace: llnl.comp\n"
"        packages/\n"
"          mpich/\n"
"            package.py\n"
"      pls/\n"
"        repo.yaml  # Contains namespace: llnl.pls\n"
"        packages/\n"
"          hdf5/\n"
"            package.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:315
msgid "Uniqueness"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:317
msgid ""
"Spack cannot ensure global uniqueness of all namespaces, but it will prevent "
"you from registering two repositories with the same namespace *at the same "
"time* in your current configuration. If you try to add a repository that has "
"the same namespace as an already registered one, Spack will print a warning "
"and may ignore the new addition or apply specific override logic depending "
"on the configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:323
msgid "Namespace Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:325
msgid ""
"Suppose LLNL maintains its own version of ``mpich`` (in a repository with "
"namespace ``llnl.comp``), separate from Spack's built-in ``mpich`` package "
"(namespace ``builtin``). If you've installed both, ``spack find`` alone "
"might be ambiguous:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:328
msgid ""
"$ spack find\n"
"==> 2 installed packages.\n"
"-- linux-rhel6-x86_64 / gcc@4.4.7 -------------\n"
"mpich@3.2  mpich@3.2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:335
msgid "Using ``spack find -N`` displays packages with their namespaces:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:337
msgid ""
"$ spack find -N\n"
"==> 2 installed packages.\n"
"-- linux-rhel6-x86_64 / gcc@4.4.7 -------------\n"
"builtin.mpich@3.2  llnl.comp.mpich@3.2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:344
msgid ""
"Now you can distinguish them. Packages differing only by namespace will have "
"different hashes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:347
msgid ""
"$ spack find -lN\n"
"==> 2 installed packages.\n"
"-- linux-rhel6-x86_64 / gcc@4.4.7 -------------\n"
"c35p3gc builtin.mpich@3.2  itoqmox llnl.comp.mpich@3.2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:354
msgid ""
"All Spack commands that take a package :ref:`spec <sec-specs>` also accept a "
"fully qualified spec with a namespace, allowing you to be specific:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:356
msgid "$ spack uninstall llnl.comp.mpich"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:361
msgid "Search Order and Overriding Packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:363
msgid ""
"When Spack resolves an unqualified package name (e.g., ``mpich`` in ``spack "
"install mpich``), it searches the configured repositories in the order they "
"appear in the *merged* ``repos.yaml`` configuration (from highest to lowest "
"precedence scope, and top to bottom within each file). The first repository "
"found that provides the package will be used. For Git-based mono-repos, the "
"individual repositories listed in its ``spack-repo-index.yaml`` are "
"effectively inserted into this search order based on the mono-repo's "
"position."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:367
msgid ""
"This search order allows you to override built-in packages. If you have your "
"own ``mpich`` in a repository ``my_custom_repo``, and ``my_custom_repo`` is "
"listed before ``builtin`` in your ``repos.yaml``, Spack will use your "
"version of ``mpich`` by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:370
msgid ""
"Suppose your effective (merged) ``repos.yaml`` implies the following order:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:372
msgid "``proto`` (local repo at ``~/my_spack_repos/spack_repo/proto_repo``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:373
msgid "``llnl`` (local repo at ``/usr/local/repos/spack_repo/llnl_repo``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:374
msgid "``builtin`` (Spack's default packages from ``spack/spack-packages``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:376
msgid "And the packages are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:379
msgid "Namespace"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:379
msgid "Source"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:379
msgid "Packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:381
msgid "``proto``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:381
msgid "``~/my_spack_repos/spack_repo/proto_repo``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:381
msgid "``mpich``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:383
msgid "``llnl``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:383
msgid "``/usr/local/repos/spack_repo/llnl_repo``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:383
msgid "``hdf5``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:385
msgid "``builtin``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:385
msgid "`spack/spack-packages` (Git)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:385
msgid "``mpich``, ``hdf5``, others"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:388
msgid "If ``hdf5`` depends on ``mpich``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:390
msgid ""
"``spack install hdf5`` will install ``llnl.hdf5 ^proto.mpich``. Spack finds "
"``hdf5`` first in ``llnl``. For its dependency ``mpich``, Spack searches "
"again from the top, finding ``mpich`` first in ``proto``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:394
msgid ""
"You can force a particular repository's package using a fully qualified name:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:396
msgid ""
"``spack install hdf5 ^builtin.mpich`` will install ``llnl.hdf5 ^builtin."
"mpich``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:397
msgid ""
"``spack install builtin.hdf5 ^builtin.mpich`` will install ``builtin.hdf5 "
"^builtin.mpich``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:399
msgid ""
"To see which repositories will be used for a build *before* installing, use "
"``spack spec -N``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:401
msgid ""
"$ spack spec -N hdf5\n"
"llnl.hdf5@1.10.0\n"
"    ^proto.mpich@3.2\n"
"    ^builtin.zlib@1.2.8"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:410
msgid ""
"While you *can* use a fully qualified package name in a ``depends_on`` "
"directive within a ``package.py`` file (e.g., ``depends_on(\"proto."
"hdf5\")``), this is **strongly discouraged**. It makes the package non-"
"portable and tightly coupled to a specific repository configuration, "
"hindering sharing and composition of repositories. A package will fail to "
"load if the hardcoded namespace's repository is not registered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:417
msgid "The ``spack repo`` Command"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:419
msgid "Spack provides commands to manage your repository configurations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:424
msgid "``spack repo list``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:426
msgid ""
"This command shows all repositories Spack currently knows about, including "
"their namespace, API version, and resolved path (local path or clone "
"directory for Git repos)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:428
msgid ""
"$ spack repo list\n"
"[+] my_local           v2.0    /path/to/spack_repo/my_local_packages\n"
"[+] comp_sci_packages  v2.0    ~/.spack/package_repos/<hash 1>/spack_pkgs/"
"spack_repo/comp_sci_packages\n"
"[+] physics_packages   v2.0    ~/.spack/package_repos/<hash 1>/spack_pkgs/"
"spack_repo/physics_packages  # From the same git repo\n"
"[+] builtin            v2.0    ~/.spack/package_repos/<hash 2>/repos/"
"spack_repo/builtin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:436
msgid ""
"Spack shows a green ``[+]`` next to each repository that is available for "
"use. It shows a red ``[-]`` to indicate that package repositories cannot be "
"used due to an error (e.g., unsupported API version, missing ``repo.yaml``, "
"etc.). It can also show just a gray ``-`` if it is a Git-based package "
"repository that has not been cloned yet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:440
msgid ""
"Note that for Git-based package repositories, ``spack repo list`` will show "
"entries for *each* individual package repository registered via ``spack-repo-"
"index.yaml``. This contrasts with ``spack config get repos``, which shows "
"the raw configuration from ``repos.yaml`` files, including just the Git URL "
"for a mono-repo:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:443
msgid ""
"$ spack config get repos\n"
"repos:\n"
"  my_local_packages: /path/to/spack_repo/my_local_packages\n"
"  example_mono_repo: https://example.com/my_org/my_pkgs.git # contains two "
"package repositories\n"
"  builtin:\n"
"    git: https://github.com/spack/spack-packages.git\n"
"    # destination: /my/custom/path (if set by user)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:456
msgid "``spack repo create``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:458
msgid "To create the directory structure for a new, empty local repository:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:460
msgid ""
"$ spack repo create ~/my_spack_projects myorg.projectx\n"
"==> Created repo with namespace 'myorg.projectx'.\n"
"==> To register it with spack, run this command:\n"
"  spack repo add ~/my_spack_projects/spack_repo/myorg/projectx"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:467
msgid "This command creates the following structure:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:469
msgid ""
"~/my_spack_projects/\n"
"  spack_repo/\n"
"    myorg/\n"
"      projectx/\n"
"        repo.yaml      # Contains namespace: myorg.projectx\n"
"        packages/      # Empty directory for new package.py files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:478
msgid ""
"The ``<target_dir>`` is where the ``spack_repo/<namespace_parts>`` hierarchy "
"will be created. The ``<namespace>`` can be simple (e.g., ``myrepo``) or "
"nested (e.g., ``myorg.projectx``), and Spack will create the corresponding "
"directory structure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:484
msgid "``spack repo add``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:486
msgid ""
"To register package repositories from local paths or a remote Git "
"repositories with Spack:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:488
msgid ""
"**For a local path:** Provide the path to the repository's root directory "
"(the one containing ``repo.yaml`` and ``packages/``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:490
msgid ""
"$ spack repo add ~/my_spack_projects/spack_repo/myorg/projectx\n"
"==> Added repo to config with name 'myorg.projectx'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:495
msgid "**For a Git repository:** Provide the Git URL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:497
msgid ""
"$ spack repo add --name my_pkgs https://github.com/spack/spack-packages.git "
"~/my_pkgs\n"
"Cloning into '/home/user/my_pkgs'...\n"
"==> Added repo to config with name 'my_pkgs'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:503
msgid ""
"Notice that for Git-based package repositories, you need to specify a "
"configuration name explicitly, which is the key used in your ``repos.yaml`` "
"configuration file. The example also shows providing a custom destination "
"path ``~/my_pkgs``. You can omit this if you want Spack to use the default "
"clone location (e.g., ``~/.spack/package_repos/<hashed_name>``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:507
msgid ""
"After adding, packages from this repository should appear in ``spack list`` "
"and be installable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:512
msgid "``spack repo remove``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:514
msgid ""
"To unregister a repository, use its configuration name (the key in ``repos."
"yaml``) or its local path."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:516
msgid "By configuration name (e.g., ``projectx`` from the add example):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:518
msgid ""
"$ spack repo remove projectx\n"
"==> Removed repository 'projectx'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:523
msgid "By path (for a local repo):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:525
msgid ""
"$ spack repo remove ~/my_spack_projects/spack_repo/myorg/projectx\n"
"==> Removed repository '/home/user/my_spack_projects/spack_repo/myorg/"
"projectx'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:530
msgid ""
"This command removes the corresponding entry from your ``repos.yaml`` "
"configuration. It does *not* delete the local repository files or any cloned "
"Git repositories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:536
msgid "``spack repo set``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:538
msgid ""
"For Git-based repositories, this command allows you to specify a custom "
"local directory where Spack should clone the repository, or use an existing "
"clone. The ``<config_name>`` is the key used in your ``repos.yaml`` file for "
"that Git repository (e.g., ``builtin``, ``my_remote_repo``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:541
msgid ""
"$ spack repo set --destination /my/custom/path/for/spack-packages builtin\n"
"==> Updated repo 'builtin'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:546
msgid ""
"This updates your user-level ``repos.yaml``, adding or modifying the "
"``destination:`` key for the specified repository configuration name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:548
msgid "``~/.spack/repos.yaml`` after ``spack repo set``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:548
msgid ""
"repos:\n"
"  builtin:\n"
"    destination: /my/custom/path/for/spack-packages\n"
"    # The 'git:' URL is typically inherited from Spack's default "
"configuration for 'builtin'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:557
msgid ""
"Spack will then use ``/my/custom/path/for/spack-packages`` for the "
"``builtin`` repository. If the directory doesn't exist, Spack will clone "
"into it. If it exists and is a valid Git repository, Spack will use it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:562
msgid "Repository Namespaces and Python"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:564
msgid ""
"Package repositories in Spack (from ``api: v2.0`` or newer) are structured "
"to integrate smoothly with Python's import system. They are effectively "
"Python namespace packages under the top-level ``spack_repo`` namespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:567
msgid ""
"The ``api: v2.0`` repository structure ensures that packages can be imported "
"using a standard Python module path: ``spack_repo.<namespace>.packages."
"<package_name>.package``. For instance, the ``mpich`` package from the "
"``builtin`` repository corresponds to the Python module ``spack_repo.builtin."
"packages.mpich.package``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:570
msgid ""
"This allows you to easily extend or subclass package classes from other "
"repositories in your own ``package.py`` files:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:572
msgid ""
"# In a package file (e.g. my_custom_mpich/package.py) in your custom repo\n"
"# Import the original Mpich class from the 'builtin' repository\n"
"from spack_repo.builtin.packages.mpich.package import Mpich as BuiltinMpich\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class MyCustomMpich(BuiltinMpich):\n"
"    # Override versions, variants, or methods from BuiltinMpich\n"
"    version(\"3.5-custom\", sha256=\"...\")\n"
"\n"
"    # Add a new variant\n"
"    variant(\"custom_feature\", default=False, description=\"Enable my "
"custom feature\")\n"
"\n"
"    def install(self, spec, prefix):\n"
"        if \"+custom_feature\" in spec:\n"
"            # Do custom things\n"
"            pass\n"
"        super().install(spec, prefix)  # Call parent install method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../repositories.rst:592
msgid ""
"Spack manages Python's ``sys.path`` at runtime to make these imports "
"discoverable across all registered repositories. This capability is powerful "
"for creating derivative packages or slightly modifying existing ones without "
"copying entire package files."
msgstr ""
